==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trebucket
<hw>Tre"buck*et</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>trebuchet</ets>,
<ets>trebukiet</ets>, an engine of war for hurling stones, F.
<ets>tr⟦eacute⟧buchet</ets> a gin, trap, a kind of balance, fr. OF.
<ets>trebuchier</ets>, <ets>trebuquier</ets>, to stumble, trip, F.
<ets>tr⟦eacute⟧bucher</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cucking stool; a
tumbrel.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A military engine used in the Middle Ages for
throwing stones, etc. It acted by means of a great weight fastened to
the short arm of a lever, which, being let fall, raised the end of the
long arm with great velocity, hurling stones with much force. </def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1534 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A kind of balance for weighing.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trecentist</ent>⟦br⟧
